Reasoning: The paper discusses compressed sensing decoders and their theoretical properties for recovering sparse and compressible signals from incomplete and inaccurate measurements. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of non-convex optimization methods also suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, which further supports the likelihood of cs.LG being a relevant sub-category.
